===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*-wós}}
From {{der|en|ML.|transformātīvus|t=transformative}}, from {{der|en|la|trānsfōrmātus|t=transformed}} + {{m|la|-īvus|pos={{glossary|suffix}} attached to the {{glossary|perfect}} {{glossary|passive}} {{glossary|participial}} {{glossary|stem}}s of {{glossary|verb}}s, forming {{glossary|deverbal}} {{glossary|adjective}}s meaning ‘doing or related to doing [''the verb'']’}}. {{m|la||Trānsfōrmātus}} is the perfect passive participle of {{m|la|trānsfōrmō|t=to transform}}, from {{m|la|trāns-|pos={{glossary|prefix}} meaning ‘across; beyond; through’}} + {{m|la|fōrmō|t=to fashion, form, format, shape}} (from {{m|la|fōrma|t=appearance, figure, form, shape}}; further etymology unknown, perhaps related to {{cog|grc|μορφή|t=a form, shape}}).<ref>{{R:OED Online|pos=v|id=204745|date=June 2018|nodot=1}}; {{R:Lexico|pos=v}}</ref> The English word is analysable as {{suffix|en|transform|ative}}.

